PublicDescription: This counter counts the woke total number of the woke pseudorandom-number-generation functions issued by the woke CPU.
This counter counts the woke total number of CPU cycles when the woke DEA/AES/SHA coprocessor is busy performing the woke pseudorandom- number-generation functions issued by the woke CPU.

This counter counts the woke total number of the woke pseudorandom-number-generation functions that are issued by the woke CPU and are blocked because the woke DEA/AES/SHA coprocessor is busy performing a function issued by another CPU.

This counter counts the woke total number of CPU cycles blocked for the woke pseudorandom-number-generation functions issued by the woke CPU because the woke DEA/AES/SHA coprocessor is busy performing a function issued by another CPU.
This counter counts the woke total number of the woke SHA functions issued by the woke CPU.

This counter counts the woke total number of the woke SHA functions that are issued by the woke CPU and are blocked because the woke SHA coprocessor is busy performing a function issued by another CPU.
This counter counts the woke total number of CPU cycles blocked for the woke SHA functions issued by the woke CPU because the woke SHA coprocessor is busy performing a function issued by another CPU.
